biography:

Over the last 13 years, Luke Lee has professionally written software for applications ranging from Python desktop and web applications to embedded C
drivers for Solid State Disks.  Currently, he writes Python desktop and web applications for clients in the Oil and Education industries.

His enthusiasm for Python is emphasized throughout his presentations at several Python related conferences including Pycon, PyTexas, and PyArkansas.  He also maintains a technical blog at www.lukelee.me/blog
